        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: note built-in dreaming is memory-core scoped; LanceDB users check ClawHub",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a short \"LanceDB and dreaming\" note to `docs/concepts/dreaming.md`:\n\n- Slot-owned plugins (e.g. memory-lancedb) may expose dreaming **settings** when they own `plugins.slots.memory`.\n- That is not the same as LanceDB-**vector-native** dreaming; for that, users browse community plugins on ClawHub.\n\nGeneric only — no package names, install scripts, hooks, or release links.\n\nCloses #87535\n\n---\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Docs-only clarification (no runtime code change).\n\n**Why this wording:** Matches OpenClaw 2026.5.27 source — `resolveMemoryDreamingPluginConfig` reads dreaming config from the memory-slot owner; tests cover memory-lancedb owning the slot. The note separates that from optional LanceDB-vector dreaming plugins discoverable on ClawHub.\n\n**Environment (author production, for context only — not claimed as proof of core docs behavior):** OpenClaw 2026.5.27, LanceDB Pro, 1000+ vectors.\n\n**Steps to reproduce:** N/A — documentation change only.\n\n**Observed result:** The added text matches shipped slot-owned config behavior and does not endorse a specific third-party package.\n\n**Not tested:** openclaw.ai docs site render (markdown only).",
